Sometimes, It’s Time to Write a New Story

There are moments in life when everything feels like it’s falling apart—when the weight of loss, pain, and uncertainty becomes too heavy to carry. But maybe, just maybe, these moments aren’t endings. Instead, they’re opportunities to write a new chapter, or even start a whole new story. 

We are reminded that God makes all things new (Revelation 21:5). Sometimes, that includes our stories. It’s okay to begin again, to walk forward in faith, trusting that life’s beauty lies not just in the easy parts, but in the struggles, too. 

Even in the darkest valleys, God’s grace is present. There is beauty in the tragedies and losses—beauty that softens the heart, builds strength, and deepens faith. Holistic health teaches us that true well-being involves embracing all parts of life, trusting that every experience is a step toward healing. 

Life is meant to be lived fully, to be embraced with open arms. Love, the ultimate goal, threads through every moment. Whether you’re facing brokenness or renewal, God’s love is the constant that holds you. As you walk this path, remember: it’s never too late to start over.

Craving fried pork chops without the carbs? This  low carb/keto friendly recipe offers a crispy, flavorful experience that won't derail your diet.

Ingredients:
 * 4 bone-in pork chops
 * 1 cup crushed pork rinds
 * 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese
 * 1 teaspoon garlic powder
 * 1/2 teaspoon onion powder
 * 1/4 teaspoon salt
 * 1/4 teaspoon black pepper
 * 2 tablespoons butter
 * 1 tablespoon olive oil
 * 1/4 cup heavy cream
 * 1/4 cup chicken broth
 * 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce

Instructions:
 * Prep the Pork Chops: Pound the pork chops to an even thickness. In a shallow bowl, combine the crushed pork rinds, Parmesan cheese, garlic powder, onion powder, salt, and pepper. Dip the pork chops in the mixture, ensuring they are evenly coated.
 * Cook the Pork Chops: Heat the butter and olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the coated pork chops and cook for 3-4 minutes per side, or until golden brown and cooked through. Remove the pork chops from the skillet and set aside.
 * Make the Gravy: In the same skillet, add the heavy cream, chicken broth, and Worcestershire sauce. Bring to a simmer and cook for 2-3 minutes, or until the sauce thickens. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
 * Serve: Return the pork chops to the skillet with the gravy and let them simmer for a few minutes to allow the flavors to meld. Serve immediately.

Macro Breakdown per Serving:
 * Calories: Approximately 450
 * Protein: Approximately 35g
 * Fat: Approximately 30g
 * Carbohydrates: Approximately 5g

Note: Macros may vary slightly depending on the specific ingredients and brands used.

Un flujo sanguíneo óptimo es esencial para la salud cardiovascular y para la función adecuada de todos los sistemas del cuerpo. 👉 Oxigenación Mejorada

When we hear the word “stress” we usually think of situations that make us nervous and affect our emotions. But these situations are just one example of the three types of stress that we all encounter in our lives.

In the professional field, chiropractors identify three types of stress that directly affect the proper functioning of our nervous system and our well-being ⤵️

💙 Emotional stress. This type of stress is the best known and the one that everyone talks about. Emotional stress can appear due to personal and professional responsibilities in our daily lives; events that can cause us anxiety, such as an exam; or also due to suffering from specific traumatic events such as a period of mourning, moving or divorce.

💙 Chemical stress. Chemical stress is less obvious than emotional stress, but it is just as important due to its consequences. Chemical stress includes all the particles that enter our organism and influence the body, such as the quality of the water we drink, the food - organic or not - we eat daily, the air we breathe or the medication we take. The clearest example of a chemical stress present that affects the majority of the population is the consumption of alcohol, tobacco, caffeine or drugs.

💙 Physical stress. Physical stress is caused by repetitive movements. Normally accompanied by bad postures at work, sports, or our leisure time; such as spending too much time in front of the computer, doing loading and unloading movements, reading... Physical stress can also be caused by specific events that directly affect our spine, such as accidents or other physical traumas, falls, blows, sports injuries, traffic accidents, etc.

La quiropráctica es un tipo de atención médica que se centra en la columna vertebral y el sistema nervioso. Incluye manipulación manual de la columna vertebral para ayudar a mejorar la función del cuerpo y aliviar el dolor. El cuidado quiropráctico alivia el dolor al restaurar la propiocepción y la movilidad de la columna vertebral. Cuando la columna vertebral está hipomóvil o no se mueve correctamente, puede poner estrés sobre los receptores nerviosos  y causar dolor. Al manipular la columna vertebral, los quiroprácticos pueden aliviar ésta condición y reducir el dolor.

➡️ Hay varias ventajas del manejo quiropráctico por sobre los medicamentos para el dolor:

1. Sin efectos secundarios: A diferencia de los medicamentos para el dolor, el manejo quiropráctico no tiene asociado  el riesgo de efectos secundarios o adicción.

2. Aborda la causa raíz del dolor: El manejo quiropráctico se centra en abordar la causa raíz del dolor en lugar de tratar simplemente los síntomas. Al corregir los desequilibrios de la columna vertebral y mejorar la función del sistema nervioso, el tratamiento quiropráctico puede ayudar a reducir el dolor agudo o crónico.

3. Promueve el bienestar general: El tratamiento quiropráctico también puede mejorar la salud general y bienestar promoviendo una mejor postura, mejorando el rango de movimiento y reduciendo el estrés en el cuerpo.

On World Mental Health Day, we recognize the struggles of those living with mental health conditions that can bring difficulties to daily life.

Mental health includes our emotional, psychological, and social well-being. It affects how we think, feel, and act, and helps determine how we handle stress, relate to others, and make choices. These conditions can deeply impact day-to-day living. Over the course of a person’s life, if you experience mental health challenges, your thinking, mood, and behavior could be affected.

Nutrition plays an important role in maintaining mental health – fruits, vegetables, grains, and herbs, spices, and teas are especially high in a group of compounds called polyphenols, which are vital to our mental health and help prevent diseases. Most days, try to avoid sugary greasy, and ultra processed foods, as well as alcohol.
To learn more about how to care for your mental health, visit
glwd.org/NutritionPortal to learn from our Registered Dietitian Nutritionists.

#WorldMentalHealthDay #MentalHealth #SelfCare

We are delighted to announce that the God’s Love We Deliver Executive Team is adding two new members: Terrence Meck as Chief Strategy & Growth Officer and Kevin Popa as Chief Human Resources Officer.

Terrence Meck joined our board of directors in 2011, serving as Chair for four years, and leaving an indelible mark on the organization. During his tenure on the Board, Terrence supported God’s Love through an era of tremendous growth: we delivered our 30 millionth meal; doubled the number of meals we delivered annually; moved into our new SoHo headquarters, the Michael Kors Building; expanded to the historic Northern Dispensary; launched the benefit concert Love Rocks NYC; launched the young professionals group genLOVE and Culinary Council; became the exclusive charity partner for the New York City Wine & Food Festival, and so much more.
 
As Chief Strategy & Growth Officer and on the precipice of our 40 millionth meal and 40th year, Terrence will help God’s Love move into the next era of our work. Terrence will oversee strategic decisions around growth in meal production, geography, policy work, systems and more.

Kevin Popa brings more than 25 years of experience in human resources leadership, having worked in financial, legal, and professional services organizations that included supporting various philanthropic endeavors and teams within those organizations. Most recently, he served as the head of human resources of DSTG Services LLC where he led human resources for DST Global’s venture capital team and the Breakthrough Prize Foundation. His previous leadership roles include positions of increasing responsibility at Barclays, UBS, Fragomen, Del Rey, Bernsen & Loewy, and Teneo.
 
With a strong leadership team in place, we embark on a new chapter filled with anticipation and renewed commitment to our shared mission. Please join us in welcoming Terrence and Kevin to our team! 👏

If I told you to stop wearing sunglasses to help you sleep better, would you do it? Let me tell you why you should:

👀 Our eyes have neurons that collect information from the sun to keep our circadian rhythm in sync with our environment.

☀️ These neurons expect lots of natural light exposure during the day. When they receive it, this signals our body to produce cortisol during the day.
 
📉 Our bodies need to produce plenty of cortisol during the day — especially in the morning — so that those levels rebound in the afternoon and stay low at night.

🏙 🌃 The difference between daytime and nighttime light exposure is important! 

💡 As we spend most of our time indoors, our bodies don’t experience a great difference between daytime and nighttime light exposure.

🤩 To better support the light exposure our bodies desire and need, drop those shades if you’re going outside and take full advantage of the natural light our neurons are expecting.

Your body is a genius. It’s so smart that it knows exactly what angle the sun should be shining upon you to stimulate Vitamin D production. 

Yep, research shows that Vitamin D is stimulated in the body when it hits your location at a 35° angle.

So how do you know when this is happening? 

I use a free app called Dminder that tells me exactly when the sun is at the optimal position for Vitamin D stimulation based on my location and time of day.

Try incorporating this strategy to your sun exposure and see what happens to your sleep.

Let’s talk sleep hygiene ladies! 💤 

It’s not just about clean sheets and comfy pillows—it’s a combo of your sleep environment and bedtime habits. Here are my top tips for ensuring you get the best sleep possible:

✨Keep it Cool, Dark, and Quiet: Set your room temp between 60-67°F, invest in blackout curtains, a sleep mask, and a sound machine to create the perfect sleep haven. (Visit my Amazon storefront linked in bio for my fave product recommendations.)

✨Declutter Your Space: Tidy up and keep distractions at bay to create a serene sleep environment.

✨Warm Lights Before Bed: Opt for warm bulbs or candlelight to stimulate melatonin production and signal to your body that it’s time to wind down.

✨Mindful Unwinding: Incorporate relaxation techniques like meditation, deep breathing, or gentle stretching to calm your mind before sleep.

✨Caffeine & Food Watch: Say no to caffeine and sugar 4-6 hours before bedtime. Opt for light snacks if hungry and avoid heavy meals.

✨Tech-Free Zone: Give your eyes a break from screens at least an hour before bedtime to reduce blue light exposure.

✨Breathe-Easy Pajamas: Wear breathable fabrics like cotton, silk, bamboo, or wool for optimal temperature regulation while you snooze.

Ever wonder why your partner likes to burn the midnight oil whereas you like to turn in early? 

The answer...chronotypes!

Chronotypes are the classification of the natural timing of your circadian rhythm.

Your circadian rhythm is essentially your body’s internal clock that guides when you’re drowsy, alert, hungry, and even influences digestion, body temperature, and wound healing (and the list keeps growing).

We used to think there were only two chronotypes: night owls and early birds. But we know humans are much more complicated than that. 

Luckily for us, world-renowned sleep expert Dr. Michael Breus has expanded upon those definitions and has identified four main chronotypes: the lion, the bear, the wolf, and the dolphin.

The key to good sleep is to go to bed with a quiet mind, for your body to feel safe, cortisol to be low, melatonin to be high, as well as sleep pressure. Your bedtime routine should facilitate the equation.

My Bedtime Routine:

⓵ Put my phone to “bed” at dinner time so I’m not tempted to check messages. I’m passionate about helping my clients and if I see a message from them at night, my brain starts working.

⓶ Take a bath with epsom salts. This primes the body for a drop in core body temperature, which is key for inducing sleep. The epsom salts provide an extra dose of much-needed magnesium to help calm my mind and body.

⓷ I also do my skincare routine by candlelight. Low warm light helps signal the brain that it’s time to wind down for the evening.

⓸ I journal if my mind is active. Even just writing stream-of-consciousness for 10 minutes helps to rid the brain of excess spiraling thoughts (not what you need at bedtime!)

⓹ I incorporate some deep breathing exercises or tapping to put my body in a parasympathetic state.

⓺ Lastly, I read until I’m sleepy — not just tired — and lights out.

Nothing says fall like an aromatic simmer pot 🍂 This fall simmer pot recipe was inspired  by our Spiced Pomander Candle which features notes of bitter orange, cinnamon and clove bud.

📌 Save this recipe for later 📌

Fall Simmer Pot Ingredients:

½ gallon apple cider

1-2 oranges, sliced

1 apple, sliced in rounds

1 pear, sliced in rounds

2-3 cinnamon sticks, plus additional for garnish

2 sprigs rosemary

Sprinkle of cloves, whole

2-3 star anise, whole

½ teaspoon vanilla extract

1 tablespoon brown sugar

Instructions:

1. Add apple cider to a large dutch oven, then add in all remaining ingredients, stirring to combine.
2. Set pot over medium high heat and bring to a boil, then reduce heat and continue simmering for at least 20-25 minutes until fragrant and slightly reduced. Continue simmering for 2-3 hours if desired, adding water as needed.
3. Ladle into mugs with any fruit slices and garnish with an additional cinnamon stick.

Today, we’re bringing back #BuyBlack Friday – one of my favorite campaigns on Facebook and Instagram. We started #BuyBlack Friday last year to harness some of the energy from the biggest physical retail day of the year in support of Black-owned small businesses. In the US, Black-owned businesses have been among the hardest hit by the pandemic, and this holiday season will be make or break for many. More than a third of US Black-owned businesses expect to make at least half of their annual revenue in the last three months of the year. 

The #BuyBlack Friday Show starts today on the Facebook Shop tab, hosted by NY Times best-selling author, journalist, and TV host @elainewelteroth, with new episodes every Friday in November. It includes Live Shopping experiences that feature Black-owned small businesses and creators and celebrate Black culture. You’ll also be able to find great ideas for presents and stocking fillers in our #BuyBlack Friday gift guide collections, which are available all month long in both the Facebook and Instagram Shop tabs. 

Among the businesses we’re showcasing is @obianaturals from Richardson, Texas. Obia Ewah is a chemist who has used her training to create her own all natural skincare products. Obia was diagnosed with thyroid cancer while at medical school at the age of 26. Looking into the cause of her cancer led her to examine the chemicals that go into many skincare products and inspired her to make her own healthy alternatives. Her creams and lotions have been a big hit, winning awards and building a loyal following. Obia also supports other local businesses and her community, starting a program called Haircuts for the Homeless, where she works with local barbers who volunteer their time. #obianaturals

The most exciting way to fly-fish for bass and panfish is to use topwater bugs, but sometimes the fish may not want to commit to eating a surface fly. In this case, try a Popper-Dropper setup. The commotion caused by the popper  attracts the fishes' attention, and then they see a tasty nymph hanging there. You'll be surprised by just how effective this technique can be.

For much more how-to information on fly-fishing for bass, visit the Orvis Fly Fishing Learning Center by clicking the link in our story.

For all our post partum queens, this is for you ❤️ 

4 things I wish I knew post partum ♥️💭 - @laurensimpson

✨Breastfeeding isn’t always easy. What is assumed a very natural process that happens smoothly - actually isn’t the case for A LOT of people. For us, Sailor has allergies…so my journey breast feeding was cut short. Which is so so okay…fed is best.

✨Post partum body changes. You may feel ‘foreign’ in your own body. You may still look pregnant weeks after as your uterus still has to shrink down to size. Be gentle with yourself.

✨It’s okay to ask for help! You don’t have to handle everything alone. As they say it takes a village. Mums need a break to to be able to fill up our own cup and look after our physical and mental well being. Lean on your support system. It doesn’t make you any less of a ‘super mum’!

✨Sleep deprivation is real. However I found that your body does somewhat adjust to the broken/less sleep. You also just show up and do what you need to daily, despite being tired!

Mummas what would you add to this list????⬇️

'The assortment of glute exercises are all over the place these days. RDLs is where it’s at & just ONE of my top 5 exercises for training your glutes😍

We felt the radiant warmth of a Greek welcome last weekend. Scenes from Ace Hotel & Swim Club Athens opening party on Saturday night, which saw family, friends, neighbours and artists whose works hang in the hotel, gather for a cultural ribbon cutting. The wine was plentiful and Greek phenom Tamta performed a secret set. And, since it isn’t over until someone jumps in the pool, Tamta’s dancers’ grand finale included an inaugural plunge. The night is now myth — thank you @officialtamta for setting the bar so high.

📷 @gerasimoupinelopi

This week @nomacph returned to Ace Hotel Kyoto. 
There’s nothing like watching them nimbly at work in our kitchen. Or seeing you savor their bardic account of autumnal abundance, embracing the ephemeral foods offered in the eye of seasonal shift. We couldn’t be happier to house it all.

@kosakyoto will return from a short hibernation following noma’s December finale. See you soon.

Images by @mitsuru_wakabayashi.

Cole Palmer explains his iconic “cold” celebration, saying it’s his way of expressing the joy and passion 🏴󠁧󠁢󠁥󠁮󠁧󠁿🥶

Cole Palmer: “I first did the ‘cold’ celebration last December in a game against Luton where we won 3-2. It’s a nod to my former City academy team-mate Morgan Rogers [who is now at Aston Villa].” 👏

“It symbolises joy, passion and hard determination for the game plus it’s funny as it works well with my name. Everyone knows it’s my celebration. Lots of people might have done it, but everybody knows it is my celebration.” 🥶

Scoop yourself some cereal, slurp up some milk, and stay fueled up all weekend long. 🥣 

Send this to someone so they have to do this.

#ProteinSnack #SnackHack #CerealDrawer #SnackInspo

Peanut butter cups and it’s the same, but they’re high protein so it’s not. You can make these easy, deliciously scrumptious peanut butter cereal bites with only 6 ingredients. 😋 Or just watch the video and imagine you were eating them for a less fulfilling, but still enjoyable experience.

🍫 Ingredients:
1 cup peanut butter
1/3 cup maple syrup
¼ cup virgin coconut oil
1 teaspoon vanilla extract
Pinch of salt
3 cups of Magic Spoon Peanut Butter cereal
3.5 oz 70% dark chocolate bar, broken up into pieces

🥜 Directions:
1. Chop half the cereal and add to a large bowl

2. Heat peanut butter, coconut oil and maple syrup in a medium pot

3. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla extract

4. Add mixture to the bowl and coat cereal completely

5. Pour into lined muffin tins

6. Microwave chocolate on high in 30 second intervals, stirring in-between, until melted

7. Top each cup with chocolate

8. Freeze for 30 minutes 

9. Sprinkle cups with sea salt, pop out, and enjoy!

Today, we’re bringing back #BuyBlack Friday – one of my favorite campaigns on Facebook and Instagram. We started #BuyBlack Friday last year to harness some of the energy from the biggest physical retail day of the year in support of Black-owned small businesses. In the US, Black-owned businesses have been among the hardest hit by the pandemic, and this holiday season will be make or break for many. More than a third of US Black-owned businesses expect to make at least half of their annual revenue in the last three months of the year. 

The #BuyBlack Friday Show starts today on the Facebook Shop tab, hosted by NY Times best-selling author, journalist, and TV host @elainewelteroth, with new episodes every Friday in November. It includes Live Shopping experiences that feature Black-owned small businesses and creators and celebrate Black culture. You’ll also be able to find great ideas for presents and stocking fillers in our #BuyBlack Friday gift guide collections, which are available all month long in both the Facebook and Instagram Shop tabs. 

Among the businesses we’re showcasing is @obianaturals from Richardson, Texas. Obia Ewah is a chemist who has used her training to create her own all natural skincare products. Obia was diagnosed with thyroid cancer while at medical school at the age of 26. Looking into the cause of her cancer led her to examine the chemicals that go into many skincare products and inspired her to make her own healthy alternatives. Her creams and lotions have been a big hit, winning awards and building a loyal following. Obia also supports other local businesses and her community, starting a program called Haircuts for the Homeless, where she works with local barbers who volunteer their time. #obianaturals

POV: you just won our GIVEAWAY and immediately made this Funfetti candy cake. Head to our giveaway post and enter before time runs out! 🍰🍬⁠
⁠
We’re dropping the FULL recipe below to save for later📩⁠
⁠
You’ll need...⁠
2 boxes Funfetti Premium Cake & Cupcake Mix⁠
Additional ingredients to prepare cake mix per box instructions⁠
3-4 tubs Funfetti Vanilla Flavored Frosting⁠
1 bag Original Smarties®⁠
1 package Giant Smarties®⁠
1 package Smarties® Candy Necklaces⁠
⁠
Directions:⁠
1. Prepare cake mix according to box instructions. Divide batter between 3 8” round pans and bake. Cool completely. Optional: Level cakes with a serrated knife to remove rounded tops of cakes.⁠
⁠
2. Frost and layer cake, using vanilla frosting in between each layer, using an offset spatula, cake scraper or butter knife. Frost the sides of the cake. Place into the fridge for 20-30 to chill. Remove from fridge.⁠
⁠
3. Unwrap Giant Smarties® and decorate the bottom of the cake by placing Giant Smarties® directly onto the cake for two layers.⁠
⁠
4. Unwrap Smarties® Candy Necklaces and attach to the cake side as desired to decorate. Unwrap Original Smarties® and add to the sides of the cake to decorate.⁠
⁠
5. Decorate the top of the cake with sprinkles from frosting lids. Top with additional wrapped Smarties® candies as desired. Serve and enjoy!⁠
⁠

Skincare actives are ingredients in skincare products that have specific functions, like exfoliating dead skin cells, hydrating the skin, or targeting skin concerns like acne or aging. Examples include ingredients such as hyaluronic acid for hydration, salicylic acid for acne, or retinol for anti-aging. Using too many of these ingredients at once can overwhelm your skin, so it’s best to introduce them gradually and monitor how your skin reacts.
✨
Using a face mask once a week helps to deeply clean your skin, remove impurities, and keep it hydrated. It also gives your skin a boost by gently removing dead skin cells and providing targeted treatment for specific concerns like acne or dryness. Plus, it’s a relaxing way to take care of yourself and enhance your skincare routine.

As we approach the end of the third quarter, it's crucial to stay on top of your financial game. Here are 5 Quick Tips to Prepare for Q4:

1. **Review Financial Statements:** Ensure your balance sheet, income statement, and cash flow are updated and accurate.
2. **Evaluate Your Budget:** Make any necessary adjustments now to avoid financial surprises later.
3. **Tax Planning:** Start considering year-end tax strategies to minimize liability.
4. **Cash Flow Projections:** Forecast your cash flow to ensure you have enough liquidity through the year-end.
5. **Consult Your Accountant:** Schedule a consultation to discuss strategic moves for the last quarter of the year.

Stay financially fit and finish the year strong! 💼📈

How Proposition 33 Could Impact Real Estate – What You Need to Know?

Proposition 33 on the November 5th ballot could change the way rent control works in California. If passed, it would allow local governments to expand rent control on newer properties and single-family homes—potentially affecting property values, new construction, and the housing market.

Not sure what this means for you? Whether you're a renter, homeowner, or investor, these changes could have serious ripple effects. Swipe through to learn more about what’s at stake and why your vote matters.

For freelance creatives, encountering slow periods is inevitable. While these lulls are challenging, they also present an opportunity to grow, improve, and prepare for the future. 

“No matter how talented you think you might be, the reality of freelance life/culture is there will always be lulls of work; it's just the nature of the beast,” says branding designer @alan_cheetham_. 

We asked experienced designers from #Behance about overcoming the slump and their advice for staying productive when work slows down.�Read the full article on the Behance blog in our bio link.

Earlier this year, Al Williams, our VP of Corporate Affairs, was invited to talk with the students at Club 61’s leadership summit. He discussed the importance of community and leadership with Chris Paul and one of the foundation’s managers. Club 61 honors Chris's grandfather, Nathaniel Jones, one of the first Black men in North Carolina to own a Chevron gas station. Chris and his brother worked there, learning valuable life lessons that shaped their leadership.

We wish Chris good luck this season and stay tuned to hear the rest of the story soon!

Kyle Denny was offered a chance to help test a new technology meant to protect people working in extreme conditions.

Witness the irresistible allure of traditional Chinese gold making as our House’s craftsmen shared their expertise live at our Gold Craftsmanship Exhibition in Beijing. From hammering to filigree, the showcase brought ancient traditions to life — a true testament to our passion for artistry and cultural preservation.

非凡造詣
工藝大師在北京活動上示範栩栩如生的黃金工藝，展示出製作中國傳統黃金的迷人魅力。從錘揲到金絲的技藝，透過工匠之手將傳統融入現代生活，見證品牌對追求中華文化藝術的熱情。

#ChowTaiFook #CTF95 #CraftingMemoriesCreatingLegacies #周大福

Quem já me conhece das antigas e conhece minha jornada sabe que 100k é um faturamento baixo comparado ao que faturo vendendo serviços e fazendo aquilo que amo fazer.

Para mim o The Box é mais um MVP que deu certo e esse é só o começo, esse ano vou exponenciar meu conhecimento e seguir ajudando mais e mais pessoas a melhorar sua vida com design.

O design tem sido visto como a solução para esses problemas. No entanto, os designers nem sempre são envolvidos no processo de criação de produtos digitais desde o início. Isso pode levar a decisões inconsistentes e a um aumento do custo de manutenção.
